    <note>Qian(1) Zhan [20416] He is not listed as a son in Yuanguan's [3042] funerary inscription, but is identified as such in Zeng(1) Gong's [7364] funerary inscription for his great granddaughter, wife of Liu(2) Huan(4) [20415] (q.v.). His son, Sheng [20417], has the generational name of Yuanguan's great grandsons, but that generation gets switched around, probably because of intermarriage with the Song imperial house. The chronology, otherwise, is correct, and I suspect that the mingzi was either changed or is just an error.</note>
